                           <list>
                              <item>
                                 <p>A manuscript, about 7 3/4 in. by 5 3/8, consisting of 85 leaves,
                                    of which <locus>foll. 21—60</locus> are vellum, the rest paper.
                                    Most of the latter are much stained and torn, especially
                                       <locus>foll. 1—13</locus>, <locus>20</locus>, and
                                       <locus>70—85</locus>. The quires, signed with both Greek and
                                    Syriac letters, seem to have been about 12 in number. Leaves are
                                    wanting at the beginning and end, as well as after <locus>foll.
                                       20</locus>, <locus>70</locus>, and <locus>77</locus>. There
                                    are from 17 to 23 lines in each page.</p>
                              </item>
                           </list>
